'''''Clear for Action''''' is a 1984 video game published by [[The Avalon Hill Game Company]].

==Gameplay==
''Clear for Action'' is a game in which up to eight players can fight battles between multiple ships, set in the era of sailing ships.<ref name="CGW20"/>

==Reception==
Floyd Mathews reviewed the game for ''[[Computer Gaming World]]'', and stated that "CFA is an entertaining game, which I recommend for both experienced and novice wargamers. Good luck, and may your swash never buckle!"<ref name="CGW20">{{cite magazine |last=Mathews |first=Floyd |title=Micro-Reviews |magazine=Computer Gaming World |date=February 1985 |volume=1 |issue=20 |pages=35â€“36}}</ref>

